            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Thanks for you amz contribution!\n\n# My issue\n1. `mini_init.lua`\n```lua\nlocal root = vim.fn.fnamemodify(\".tests\", \":p\")\n\nfor _, name in ipairs({ \"config\", \"data\", \"state\", \"cache\" }) do\n    vim.env[(\"XDG_%s_HOME\"):format(name:upper())] = root .. \"/\" .. name\nend\n\nvim.print(vim.o.rtp)\n\nvim.pack.add({\n    \"https://github.com/nvim-lua/plenary.nvim\",\n})\n\n```\n\n2. run `nvim --noplugin --headless -u mini_init.lua -c \"PlenaryBustedDirectory tests/ { minimal_init = 'mini_init.lua' }`\n\nI got these error.\n```\nE5113: Lua chunk: /usr/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/pack.lua:617: Vim:E919: Directory not found in 'packpath': \"pack/*/opt/plenary.nvim\"\nstack traceback:\n        [C]: in function 'packadd'\n        /usr/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/pack.lua:617: in function 'pack_add'\n        /usr/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/pack.lua:680: in function 'add'\n```\n\nI guess which is related reassign XDG environment variables. \n\n\nCould you add more cases about bootstrap with `vim.pack` in `pack.txt`, e.g. \n* How to bootstrap a `busted` test \n* How to write a \"standard\" repro.lua\n\nIt just like https://lazy.folke.io/developers\n\n\nThx.\n\n \n",
