            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> I guess which is related reassign XDG environment variables.\n\nYes, `vim.pack.add()` right now puts its plugins in ['$XDG_DATA_HOME/nvim/site/pack/core/opt'](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/d9465e984b34ab7f98007e52edaf1ebc0ccef038/runtime/doc/lua.txt#L2535), which is by default in 'packpath' (list of directories where `:packadd` looks for a plugin). However, it seems that the value of 'packpath' is populated and \"fixed\" before `XDG_xxx_HOME` environment variables are set. \n\nYou can work around that by appending necessary path to 'packpath'. Add this before `vim.pack.add()` call:\n\n```lua\nvim.env.NVIM_APPNAME = vim.env.NVIM_APPNAME or 'nvim'\nlocal pack_path = vim.fn.expand('$XDG_DATA_HOME/$NVIM_APPNAME/site')\nvim.o.packpath = vim.o.packpath ..',' .. pack_path\n```\n\nThe usage of `$NVIM_APPNAME` is described in `:h $NVIM_APPNAME`.",
